<DL>
<DT><PRE>public class <B>SimpleMappingExceptionResolver</B><DT>extends <A HREF="../../../../../org/springframework/web/portlet/handler/AbstractHandlerExceptionResolver.html" title="class in org.springframework.web.portlet.handler">AbstractHandlerExceptionResolver</A></DL>
</PRE>

<P>
<A HREF="../../../../../org/springframework/web/portlet/HandlerExceptionResolver.html" title="interface in org.springframework.web.portlet"><CODE>HandlerExceptionResolver</CODE></A> implementation
 that allows for mapping exception class names to view names, either for a
 set of given handlers or for all handlers in the DispatcherPortlet.

 <p>Error views are analogous to error page JSPs, but can be used with any
 kind of exception including any checked one, with fine-granular mappings for
 specific handlers.
<P>

